@page "/components/navigation/menu/standalone-item"
@layout MainLayout
@using Sunfish.UIAdapters.Blazor.Components.Showcase

<PageTitle>MenuItem / Standalone vs in-menu · Sunfish Kitchen Sink</PageTitle>

<SunfishExamplePanel Title="MenuItem / Standalone vs in-menu"
                     Breadcrumb="@_breadcrumb"
                     GitHubUrl="https://github.com/ctwoodwa/Sunfish/blob/main/apps/kitchen-sink/Pages/Components/Navigation/Menu/StandaloneItem/Demo.razor"
                     Sources="@GeneratedSources">

    <Narrative>
        <p>
            <code>SunfishMenuItem</code> is most often used as a child of <code>SunfishMenu</code>
            (or a menubar). In that scenario the item must advertise <code>role="menuitem"</code>
            so AT users can navigate the menu pattern correctly. But the same primitive can also
            be reused outside a menu &mdash; for example as a row in a custom command palette or
            a button rendered inside a popover &mdash; and in those cases an orphan
            <code>role="menuitem"</code> would trip axe's
            <a href="https://dequeuniversity.com/rules/axe/4.7/aria-required-parent"
               target="_blank" rel="noopener">
                <code>aria-required-parent</code>
            </a>
            rule.
        </p>
        <p>
            The <code>InMenu</code> parameter gates the role: it defaults to <code>false</code>
            (no role), and <code>SunfishMenu</code> sets <code>InMenu="true"</code> on its
            children when it composes them. When you mount a <code>SunfishMenuItem</code> as a
            child of <code>SunfishMenu</code> in markup directly, set <code>InMenu="true"</code>
            yourself so it inherits the menu pattern.
        </p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong><code>InMenu="false"</code> (default)</strong> &mdash; no <code>role</code> attribute, behaves as a plain button or anchor.</li>
            <li><strong><code>InMenu="true"</code></strong> &mdash; emits <code>role="menuitem"</code>; only safe when an ancestor is <code>role="menu"</code> / <code>menubar</code>.</li>
            <li><strong>WCAG mapping</strong> &mdash; SC 4.1.2 <em>Name, Role, Value</em>.</li>
        </ul>
    </Narrative>

    <Example>
        <div style="display:flex; flex-direction:column; gap:1.5rem;">

            <section>
                <h3 style="margin:0 0 .5rem;">Inside a <code>SunfishMenu</code> (set <code>InMenu="true"</code>)</h3>
                <p style="margin:.25rem 0 .5rem; color:#555; font-size:.9rem;">
                    Each item exposes <code>role="menuitem"</code> and the surrounding container
                    is <code>role="menu"</code>, satisfying the required-parent contract.
                </p>
                <div class="demo-row">
                    <SunfishButton OnClick="() => _open = !_open">File</SunfishButton>
                    <SunfishMenu IsOpen="@_open" IsOpenChanged="@((bool v) => _open = v)">
                        <SunfishMenuItem InMenu="true" Icon="plus" Text="New" />
                        <SunfishMenuItem InMenu="true" Icon="folder" Text="Open" />
                        <SunfishMenuItem InMenu="true" Icon="save" Text="Save" />
                    </SunfishMenu>
                </div>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h3 style="margin:0 0 .5rem;">Standalone (<code>InMenu="false"</code> &mdash; default)</h3>
                <p style="margin:.25rem 0 .5rem; color:#555; font-size:.9rem;">
                    Mounted outside a menu container. No <code>role="menuitem"</code> is emitted,
                    so AT users hear the items as ordinary buttons rather than as orphan menu items.
                </p>
                <div style="display:flex; flex-direction:column; gap:.25rem; max-width:240px;">
                    <SunfishMenuItem Icon="download" Text="Download report" />
                    <SunfishMenuItem Icon="share" Text="Share link" />
                    <SunfishMenuItem Icon="trash" Text="Delete" IsDisabled="true" />
                </div>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h3 style="margin:0 0 .5rem;">ARIA reference</h3>
                <dl style="display:grid; grid-template-columns: max-content 1fr; gap:.4rem 1rem; margin:0;">
                    <dt><code>role="menuitem"</code></dt>
                    <dd>Emitted only when <code>InMenu="true"</code>; <code>SunfishMenu</code> sets this for its rendered children.</dd>

                    <dt><code>aria-disabled</code></dt>
                    <dd>Set on disabled anchors. Buttons also use the native <code>disabled</code> attribute.</dd>
                </dl>
            </section>

        </div>
    </Example>

</SunfishExamplePanel>

@code {
    private static readonly string[] _breadcrumb =
        ["Components", "Navigation", "Menu", "StandaloneItem"];

    private bool _open;
}
